alert.note: Alert for Southwestern Humboldt (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Wind Advisory issued December 26 at 3:06AM PST until December 27 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 7 PM PST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...South winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph expected. Isolated gusts to 70 mph on high mountain peaks and ridges. * WHERE...Southwestern Humboldt County. * WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 7 PM PST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest gusts will be restricted to high ridges and coastal headlands exposed to the south and east.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
